The paper focuses on developing a navigation scheme for underwater robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed approach involves using visual perception cues, such as dense point cloud generation and plane representation, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The adaptive decision-making approach also suggests a potential application of machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. Finally, the paper mentions the use of the proposed approach in oil & gas production (OGP) scenarios, which involves system control and optimization (cs.SY).
